                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President of the Central American Court
                            of Justice</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                        State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San Jose, C. R.</hi>
                        </placeName> (<date
                            ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates"
                            calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1910-05-11T19:40:00-05:00"
                            notBefore="1910-05-04T00:00:00-05:00">undated</date>).<lb/>(Received May
                        11, 1910—7.40 p.m.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Central American court of justice acknowledges with sincere thanks your
                    excellency’s cablegram dated yesterday, by which you congratulate it on the
                    mediation it has rendered to secure peace in Nicaragua, and highly appreciates
                    your excellency’s wishes for the establishment of a government of order and
                    prosperity in Nicaragua.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Alberto Ucles.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
